knowledge_graph.title: Hot chocolate
knowledge_graph.description: Hot chocolate, also known as hot cocoa or drinking chocolate, is a heated drink consisting of shaved or melted chocolate or cocoa powder, heated milk or water, and usually a sweetener. It is often garnished with whipped cream or marshmallows.

related_questions.question: Is drinking hot chocolate healthy?
related_questions.snippet: The abundant antioxidants in cocoa, primarily flavonoids, contribute to cardiovascular well-being, enhancing blood flow and reducing blood pressure and cholesterol levels. These compounds also show the potential to fortify cognitive function and lift mood, offering a holistic approach to health.
related_questions.title: Health Benefits Of Hot Chocolate

related_questions.question: What is the difference between hot chocolate and hot cocoa?
related_questions.snippet: Hot Chocolate is made using solid chocolate melted in warm milk or cream. Hot Cocoa, however, is made from a powdered base of cocoa with added sugar and dissolved in hot water or hot milk.
related_questions.title: What's the difference between Hot Chocolate and Hot Cocoa?

related_questions.question: Is hot chocolate better for you than coffee?
related_questions.snippet: Mood-boosting effects: Drinking hot chocolate has been shown to increase levels of serotonin and endorphins in the brain, which can improve mood and reduce stress. A healthier option: Compared to coffee, hot chocolate contains less fat and calories and is a good source of antioxidants.
